        <abstract>
            <p>Acknowledges JS’s excellent letter of 25 September. May CD assume that the gigantic worm-casts were nearly circular when measured before the rain?</p>
            <p>That a medical man should always have the place of superintendent seems a piece of jobbery.</p>
            <p>Mentions [George] King.</p>
            <p>JS’s thin paper renders some words on other side almost illegible.</p>
        </abstract>
